history.text: Hello, the movie is Maleficent
It has a cinemascore of an A. Have you seen it?
It has Angelina Jolie as the main as Maleficent
Hi I did see this movie it was excellent.
So even though it just has a 5.7/10 you enjoyed it?
Do you generally watch movies based of ratings or don't care?
Oh wow, that's low! I would rate it as a 8/10
Yes, that was the Rotten Tomatoes score
I don't generally care about ratings as I disagree with the ratings
Did you see the movie?
yes I did see it
I enjoyed the conflict of relationships
I think it was neat that her daughter was in the movie with her
Ah yes, the struggle between good and evil!
The document compares the stereotypes to that of fozen, have you seen that movie? Do you understand what it means by that?
I did see Frozen, I guess the struggle between by the characters to do the right thing.
They put Maleficent in the superhero genre, I think thats odd, how about you?
I don't find that odd. Although she could be NOT nice, ultimately she protected Sleeping Beauty and she learned how to be kind.
Yes, but she is the one that turned Moors into a dark kingdom in the first place. Does correcting that at the end make her a hero or?
Do you think maleficent slowly started to regret what she did, or right after seeing that the pixies were failing to take care of aurora?
I believe she did that to protect herself and her heart. Once she learned how to care and love changing the the Dark Kingdom into one of light was a natural progression.
I think she started to regret her actions when she saw the love in Aurora's heart.
Do you think Aurora took the right action when she found out about maleficents true identity?
Meaning running to her fathers castle
What character pulled you into the story more maleficent or Aurora? What do you think others say about the same question?
I think she was scared and did what she could to protect herself. Maleficent pulled me into the story. I think others would say Aurora.
Others also say Maleficent.
What did you think about the dark curse pulling aurora to prick her finger? Did you like the build up even though you knew it was going to happen/
Not really that was kinda creepy. I wanted it to just be over with!
Did you like phillip?
Phillip
I forget Phillip, was he the young prince or the dad?

Phil's kiss was one who failed to awaken Aurora. 
What did you think of Stefan's death at the end?
I don't like when characters are killed in kid's movies.
I agree. Why do you think she didn't want to kill him, but he died anyway?
I'm not sure. Maybe because then the ending of the story wouldn't have made sense?
How did you feel when Aurora found her wings?
You mean Malificent's wings? I was thrilled and happy

uid2response.feedback: Good conversation regarding the movie. I want to watch the movie again!
